title: Ep. - 252 - RONNIE KARAM REVIEWS BACHELOR AND BRAVO REVIEW OF NATALIE WOOD DOCUMENTARY
description:
Ronnie Karam, Co-Host of Watch What Crappens and Rose Pricks podcasts reviews The Bachelor: Listen to Your Heart, Shahs of Sunset, Real Housewives of Beverly Hills, and Real Housewives of New York.

 

Washington Post entertainment reporter Emily Yahr reviews the documentary “Natalie Wood: What Remains Behind” on HBO, which explores actor Natalie Wood’s life and career through the unique perspective of her daughter, Natasha Gregson Wagner, and others who knew her best.
